# {{SERVER_NAME}}

## Identity

- Domain: `{{DOMAIN}}`
- Admin user: `{{ADMIN_USER}}`
- Admin email: `{{ADMIN_EMAIL}}`
- LAN IP: `{{LAN_IP}}`
- Timezone: `{{TZ}}`
- Data root: `{{DATA_ROOT}}`
- Docker network: `{{DOCKER_NET}}`

## Layout

- `{{DATA_ROOT}}/docker`: compose files and service env files
- `{{DATA_ROOT}}/data`: persistent data and service state
- `{{DATA_ROOT}}/apps/static`: static files served by Caddy
- `{{DATA_ROOT}}/backups`: local backup archives and scripts
- `{{DATA_ROOT}}/MDs`: local documentation

## Services

- Caddy
- Cloudflared
- PostgreSQL
- NocoDB at `https://{{NOCODB_SUBDOMAIN}}.{{DOMAIN}}`
- Optional n8n at `https://{{N8N_SUBDOMAIN}}.{{DOMAIN}}`
- Optional DBHub at `https://{{DBHUB_SUBDOMAIN}}.{{DOMAIN}}`
- Optional OpenClaw at `https://{{OPENCLAW_SUBDOMAIN}}.{{DOMAIN}}`

## Rules

- Back up before risky changes.
- Never serve from a source checkout.
- Keep secrets in `.env` files.
- Never rotate `N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY` once n8n has data.
